      "writtenOn": "2020-07-13T17:21:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Nit: Please use \"const\" instead of \"let\" anywhere where the variable only gets assigned once.\n\nTip: Do a massive s/let/const/ rename and only revert to \"let\" where the compiler complains about consts with multiple assignments.\n\nRationale:\n- Less potential for bugs.\n- Less cognitive load for the reader.\n- A \"let\" with just one assignment makes the reader suspect there might be a bug (the programmer must have intended to make multiple assignments but forgot to do so?)",
