      "writtenOn": "2020-07-13T17:21:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think this check can be removed because config is guaranteed to be non-null by the compiler (assuming this method is only ever called from TypeScript and not raw JavaScript).\n\nSame on the other private methods below.\n\nNote: if you actually want to allow null arguments, please declare their type as T | null, e.g.\n\n  _computeRollWindowStart(config: Config | null) { ... }",
