      "lineNbr": 663,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-14T13:53:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So, this is one of the oddities I\u0027m experiencing with TypeScript.  It\u0027s great to have all the compiler guarantees, but in the end the data is always being parsed from JSON and cast to the appropriate type.  IIUC, unless the compiler is adding code to verify that all of the fields exist and create them if not, all that safety is going out the window.  Can we actually guarantee that this field exists?\n\nconst rollerStatus \u003d \u003cStatus\u003eJSON.parse(\u0027{}\u0027);\n// According to the compiler, rollerStatus.config must exist, but it wasn\u0027t supplied above.\nthis.computeRollWindowStart(rollerStatus.config);",
      "parentUuid": "d8167429_c41d0c56",
      "range": {
